author: julianfoad
msg: Tweak some WC tests to always use SHA-1 checksums (not MD-5) in the NODES
table, and to ensure there is an entry in the PRISTINE table before
inserting a reference to it in the NODES table.  This is because I want
to enforce those rules throughout libsvn_wc later.
(TESTING_DATA): Insert a PRISTINE table row for the NODES rows to refer
to.  Adjust the NODES rows to use SHA-1 rather than MD-5 checksums.
(test_getting_info, test_inserting_nodes): Use SHA-1 rather than MD-5.
